        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 21 at 4:35PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 435 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles north of Washburn, or 9 miles west of Panhandle, moving
northwest at 5 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Panhandle, Washburn, and Pantex.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
